apply all 
> kubectl apply -f k8s-manifest-files/

watch pod come up
> kubectl watch pod -n microservice-ns

describe a pod for events and debug info
> kuectl descibe pod <pod-name> -n microservice-ns

view pod logs 
> kubectl logs <pod-name> -n microservice-ns --follow

go inside the pod 
> kubectl exec -it <pod-name> todo-app bash

check hpa status 
> kubectl get hpa -n microservice-ns

check rollout status 
> kubectl rollout status deployment/microservice-deployment -n microservice-ns

rollback to previous version
> kubectl rollout undo deployment/microservice-deployment -n  microservice-ns

port forward a pod for local hosting 
> kubectl port-forward deployment/microservice-deployment 3000:3000 -n microservice-ns